            <title>[SPARK-1446] Spark examples should not do a System.exit</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SPARK-1446</link>
                <project id="12315420" key="SPARK">Spark</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The spark examples should exit nice (sparkcontext.stop()) rather then doing a System.exit. The System.exit can cause issues like in &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SPARK-1407&quot; title=&quot;EventLogging to HDFS doesn&amp;#39;t work properly on yarn&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;SPARK-1407&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;SPARK-1407&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;.  SparkHdfsLR and JavaWordCount both do the System.exit. We should look through all the examples.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
